    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-right has-small-font-size\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/blocks/\">Go back to the list of <strong>Blocks</strong></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Cover </strong>block lets you add an image or video with a text overlay.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To add the <strong>Cover </strong>block, click the (+) icon to open the block inserter pop-up window. Look for the <em><strong>Cover </strong></em>block using the search bar and click the block icon to add it to the editor.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Alternatively, you can quickly add the <strong>Cover </strong>block by typing /cover and pressing Enter.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"598\" height=\"302\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2021/02/Screen-Shot-2021-02-23-at-10.16.40-AM.png\" alt=\"How to add the cover block to a page or post\" class=\"wp-image-14091311\" style=\"width:449px;height:227px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2021/02/Screen-Shot-2021-02-23-at-10.16.40-AM.png 598w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2021/02/Screen-Shot-2021-02-23-at-10.16.40-AM-300x152.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 598px) 100vw, 598px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">How to add the Cover block to a page or post</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/\">Detailed instructions on adding blocks</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you add the <strong>Cover block</strong>, you have a few options which are</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>You can add an image or video from your device or from the Openverse.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Choose&nbsp;<strong>Select Media</strong>&nbsp;to choose from an existing image or video on your site.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You can now select the&nbsp;<strong>Use featured image</strong>&nbsp;option to set the cover as the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wordpress.com/support/featured-images/\">featured image</a>&nbsp;of your page or post.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You can click on the colored circles to use the respective background color for your cover. You can later change it to any other color in the block settings.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Resize the <strong>Cover </strong>block by dragging the bottom border and moving it up and down.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"483\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/cover-block-1024x483.png\" alt=\"The options available to add an image to the cover block\" class=\"wp-image-16355747\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/cover-block-1024x483.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/cover-block-300x141.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/cover-block-768x362.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/cover-block.png 1340w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The options available to add an image to the Cover block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s how to use the <strong>Featured Image</strong> on the Cover block</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/Cover-block-using-featured-image.mov\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Resize option</strong> for the Cover block</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Cover block comes with a resize tooltip which appears below the Cover block when dragging. You can resize the block by moving the tooltip up and down. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/resize-coverblock.mov\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"block-toolbar\">Block toolbar</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Each block toolbar comes with different options. These block toolbars let you customize or modify the block in the editor. To view the <strong>Cover </strong>block toolbar, select the block, and it will show a list of toolbar options.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Cover </strong>block has the following tools:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Transform to</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Moving handles</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Change alignment</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Change content position</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Toggle full height</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Replace</li>\n\n\n\n<li>More options</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"852\" height=\"106\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/Screenshot-2023-03-02-at-19.34.53.png\" alt=\"Image showing the block toolbar for the block\" class=\"wp-image-16355759\" style=\"width:426px;height:53px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/Screenshot-2023-03-02-at-19.34.53.png 852w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/Screenshot-2023-03-02-at-19.34.53-300x37.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/Screenshot-2023-03-02-at-19.34.53-768x96.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 852px) 100vw, 852px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Image showing the block toolbar for the block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Transform to</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"478\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/transform-cover-block-1024x478.png\" alt=\"How to transform a cover block to a different block.\" class=\"wp-image-16355749\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/transform-cover-block-1024x478.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/transform-cover-block-300x140.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/transform-cover-block-768x359.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/transform-cover-block.png 1392w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Transform to tool allows you to convert the Cover block into the following blocks:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Columns</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Group</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Media &amp; Text</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Image</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/Cover-in-Group-1024x640.png\" alt=\"Editor view of cover as a Group with Color settings controls\" class=\"wp-image-16355750\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/Cover-in-Group-1024x640.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/Cover-in-Group-300x187.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/Cover-in-Group-768x480.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/Cover-in-Group-1536x960.png 1536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/Cover-in-Group.png 1748w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Editor view of cover as a <strong>Group</strong> with <strong>Color settings</strong> controls</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Moving handles</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"620\" height=\"84\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-2.png\" alt=\"The blog moving tool for the cover block\" class=\"wp-image-16358919\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-2.png 620w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-2-300x41.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The up and down arrow icons can be used to shift a block up and down in your document. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"617\" height=\"86\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-1.png\" alt=\"The drag and drop tool tool for the cover block\" class=\"wp-image-16358918\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-1.png 617w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-1-300x42.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 617px) 100vw, 617px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Or you can drag the six dots icon allows you to freely reposition the <strong>Cover </strong>block anywhere within the editor by holding the icon and dragging the block to the new location.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Detailed instructions on moving a block within the editor can be found&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/moving-blocks/\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Change alignment</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"806\" height=\"642\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/cover-block-alignment.png\" alt=\"Changing the alignment of the Cover block\" class=\"wp-image-16355752\" style=\"width:385px;height:306px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/cover-block-alignment.png 806w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/cover-block-alignment-300x239.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/cover-block-alignment-768x612.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 806px) 100vw, 806px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Changing the alignment of the Cover block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the Change alignment tool to modify the alignment of the <strong>Cover </strong>block. Select the tool and pick one of the following alignment options:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>None</strong> &#8211; Leaves the block the current size.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Wide width</strong>&nbsp;\u2013 Increase the width of the post beyond the content size.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Full width</strong>&nbsp;\u2013 Extend the block to cover the full width of the screen.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Align left</strong>&nbsp;\u2013 Make the block left-aligned.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Align center</strong>&nbsp;\u2013 Make the block alignment centered.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Align right&nbsp;</strong>\u2013 Make the block right aligned.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size has-heading-3-font-size\">Change content position</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"623\" height=\"85\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-5.png\" alt=\"The change content position tool for the cover block\" class=\"wp-image-16358922\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-5.png 623w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-5-300x41.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 623px) 100vw, 623px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Change content position lets you modify the position of the Paragraph block within the <strong>Cover </strong>block. You can position the Paragraph block on the top left to the bottom right of the <strong>Cover </strong>block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video aligncenter\"><video autoplay controls loop muted src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2021/02/alignment.mov\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Toggle full height</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"622\" height=\"85\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-3.png\" alt=\"The full height toggle for the cover block\" class=\"wp-image-16358920\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-3.png 622w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-3-300x41.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 622px) 100vw, 622px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This option allows the <strong>Cover block</strong> to take up the height of the reader&#8217;s screen to create an immersive experience. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video autoplay controls loop muted src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2021/02/fullheight_trimmed_720.mov\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Replace</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"625\" height=\"81\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-4.png\" alt=\"The replace button for the cover block\" class=\"wp-image-16358921\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-4.png 625w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-4-300x39.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This is another option in the <strong>Cover block&#8217;s</strong> toolbar. Choosing this will allow you to select a new image file for your block. Use this if you need to replace the image file in your <strong>Cover block</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">More options</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>These controls give you the option to copy, duplicate, and edit your block as HTML.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\">Read about these and other settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress blocks have specific configuration options in the block settings panel. To access the <strong>Cover </strong>block settings panel, click the Settings button at the top-right corner of the editor screen.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><br>The <strong>Cover </strong>block settings panel is divided into two tabs \u2013 Settings and Styles. It contains the following sections:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Layout</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"505\" height=\"412\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-6.png\" alt=\"The layout settings for the cover block\" class=\"wp-image-16358923\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-6.png 505w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-6-300x245.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 505px) 100vw, 505px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In the Layout section, you will see the following customization options:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>The <em>Inner blocks use the content width toggle</em> button, allowing nested blocks to use content width with options for full and wide widths.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The <em>Content width</em> tool lets you customize the width for all elements assigned to the center or wide columns.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Media settings</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"361\" height=\"771\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-7.png\" alt=\"The media settings for the cover block\" class=\"wp-image-16358924\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-7.png 361w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-7-140x300.png 140w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 361px) 100vw, 361px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Fixed background</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"200\" height=\"67\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/12/Screenshot54545dffd.png\" alt=\"Fixed background setting for the cover image \" class=\"wp-image-13786429\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Fixed background setting for the cover image</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In the block settings on the sidebar, you have some other options, the first of which is a toggle for a fixed background. A fixed background means the cover image scrolls along with your page. Turning this option off embeds the image in place, so the image doesn&#8217;t scroll.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video aligncenter\"><video autoplay controls loop muted src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/08/Cover87899-1.mp4\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Repeated background</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"225\" height=\"65\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/Screenshot-repeated123.png\" alt=\"Repeated background settings for the cover image\" class=\"wp-image-13786434\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Repeated background</strong> option lets you repeat the same image to form a pattern in the Cover block. For example, if you have a small image and you want it to repeat multiple times in the Cover block, you can enable this option.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video aligncenter\"><video autoplay controls loop muted src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/12/5-05cb8f618d67.mov\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can use the <strong>Repeated background</strong> toggle in combination with <strong>Fixed background</strong>, but <strong>Fixed background</strong> does not necessarily have to be turned on. Feel free to play around with these options to find what suits your needs.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Focal point picker</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"556\" height=\"662\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/cover-block-focalpoint.png\" alt=\"Focal point picker for the cover image\" class=\"wp-image-16355766\" style=\"width:278px;height:331px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/cover-block-focalpoint.png 556w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/cover-block-focalpoint-252x300.png 252w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 556px) 100vw, 556px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Focal point picker for the cover image</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If the fixed background option is turned off, you will see the focal point picker. This tool lets you identify the main point of interest in the photo and highlight. Click on the picker to drag it to the spot you want, or use the left and top position percentages below to set it manually.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The clear media button removes the media and any changes you have to it. </p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Alternative text</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>The alternative text field allows you to add an alternative text for the cover image.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Color</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"435\" height=\"320\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-8.png\" alt=\"The color settings for the cover block\" class=\"wp-image-16358925\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-8.png 435w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-8-300x221.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 435px) 100vw, 435px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With the Color settings, you can customize the <strong>Cover </strong>block by adding text, background, and link colors. The color selections vary depending on your active theme.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also add a gradient color to the <strong>Cover </strong>block. To do that, transform the block into the Media &amp; Text block. Click the Background option and select the Gradient tab. Choose a color from the list. Convert the Media &amp; Text block back into the <strong>Cover </strong>block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/colors-settings-overview/\">Learn more about the Color settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Filter options</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Filters section contains the Apply duotone filter option. So, you can enable the duotone filter from the block settings panel</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/filters-settings-overview/\">Read more about the filter options</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Dimensions</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Cover&nbsp;block </strong>provides dimension settings options to add padding and margin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\">For details refer to this support article: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/dimension-controls-overview/\">Dimension settings overview</a></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"550\" height=\"388\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/cover-block-dimensions.png\" alt=\"Dimension setting for the cover block\" class=\"wp-image-16355756\" style=\"width:275px;height:194px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/cover-block-dimensions.png 550w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/03/cover-block-dimensions-300x212.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Dimension setting for the Cover block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Typography</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Typography settings enable you to customize the font and text appearance of the content within the <strong>Cover </strong>block. The settings have various options, such as font size, font style, font family, and letter spacing. </p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\">For details refer to this support article: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/typography-settings-overview/\">Typography settings overview</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size has-heading-3-font-size\">Advanced</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Advanced</strong> tab lets you add HTML anchor and CSS class(es) to your block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"548\" height=\"856\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/cover-block-advanced.png\" alt=\"Advanced settings for the Cover block\" class=\"wp-image-16355764\" style=\"width:274px;height:428px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/cover-block-advanced.png 548w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/cover-block-advanced-192x300.png 192w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 548px) 100vw, 548px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Advanced settings for the Cover block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HTML element</strong>&nbsp;lets you choose between these HTML elements: Div, header, footer, main, section, article, and aside. It will default to div if another option isn&#8217;t selected. While more advanced, this option allows you to add semantic elements that can be used to define different parts of a web page. For example, if you&#8217;re using the Cover block as part of your Header, it would make sense to define it as such. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HTML anchor</strong> allows you to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/page-jumps/\">make a unique web address</a>&nbsp;for a particular <strong>Cover block</strong>. Then, you\u2019ll be able to link directly to a <strong>Cover block</strong> of your page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Additional CSS class(es)</strong> lets you add CSS class(es) to your block, allowing you to write custom CSS and style the block as you see fit.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group changelog has-very-dark-gray-color has-very-light-gray-background-color has-text-color has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\" id=\"changelog\">Changelog<strong> </strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated 2023-11-21\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>consistency changes for Cover block mentions in text</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2023-11-11\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated all headings to sentence case</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2023-10-04\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated for 6.3</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2023-03-27\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated video on using a featured image in a Cover block.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated information about the HTML element section. </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2023-03-02 \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Changed the screenshot to reflect the new changes </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added the Duotone filter </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Information/video about how to resize the cover block</li>\n\n\n\n<li>HTML element</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2022-12-12\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added typography and dimension settings</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2022-11-26\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Made images more mobile responsive </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added captions to images </li>\n\n\n\n<li>replaces redundant content</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2022-02-04\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Screenshots for WordPress 5.9</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2021-02-23\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Screenshots per WordPress 5.7</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added feature change to Block Toolbar: Full Height Alignment</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2020-12-14\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added Repeated background in Block Settings</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2020-08-24\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Screenshots and videos as per WordPress 5.5</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added feature changes in Block Toolbar</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added feature changes in Block Settings</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2020-06-18\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added &#8220;Go back to the list of&nbsp;Blocks&#8221; to the top of the page</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2020-04-28\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Changed Category to &#8220;Common Blocks&#8221;</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2019-11-27\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated animated GIF to video</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Created 2020-03-07</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n",
